 16class ValidatorModelABC(ABC):
 17
 18    def __init__(
 19        self,
 20        data_models_context: DataModelsContext,
 21        report_list: ModelListReport,
 22        type_class: Type[SpModelABC],
 23        **kwargs: Dict[str, Any],
 24    ):
 25        # SETUP
 26        self._data_models_context = data_models_context
 27        self._report_list = report_list
 28        self._type_class = type_class
 29
 30        # UNPACK DATA
 31        self._data_model = self._data_models_context.get_instance_of(self._type_class)
 32        self._filename = self._data_model.filename if self._data_model else "Unknown"
 33        self._dataframe = self._data_model.data_loader_model.df_data.copy() if self._data_model else pd.DataFrame({})
 34        self.TITLES_INFO = self._data_models_context.config.get_verify_names()
 35
 36        # LIST OF ERRORS AND WARNINGS
 37        self._errors: List[str] = []
 38        self._warnings: List[str] = []
 39
 40        self.init()

 45    def check_columns_in_models_dataframes(
 46        self,
 47        required_columns: Dict[str, List[str]],
 48        model_dataframes: Dict[str, pd.DataFrame],
 49    ) -> List[str]:
 50        """
 51        Check if required columns exist in the provided dataframes for different models.
 52        :param required_columns: A dictionary where keys are model names and values are lists of required column names.
 53        :param model_dataframes: A dictionary where keys are model names and values are their corresponding dataframes.
 54        :return: A list of error messages for missing columns.
 55        """
 56        errors = []
 57
 58        # Check if columns exist
 59        for model_name, columns in required_columns.items():
 60            dataframe = model_dataframes[model_name]
 61            if dataframe is not None:
 62                for column in columns:
 63                    exists_column, error_msg = self.column_exists(dataframe, model_name, column)
 64                    if not exists_column:
 65                        errors.append(error_msg)
 66
 67        return errors
 68
 69    # Create static method to check if column exists
 70    def column_exists(self, dataframe, filename, column) -> Tuple[bool, str]:
 71
 72        # How use: To use this method, you can call it directly with the dataframe and column name.
 73        exists, msg_error_column = column_exists(dataframe, filename, column)
 74        return exists, msg_error_column

 76    def _column_exists(self, column: str) -> Tuple[bool, str]:
 77        exists, msg_error_column = column_exists(self._dataframe, self._filename, column)
 78        return exists, msg_error_column

 81        exists, msg_error_column = column_exists(dataframe, self._filename, column)

 84    def _check_text_length(self, column: str, max_len: int) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 85        """Helper function to validate text length in a column."""
 86        warnings = []

 90            column=column,

104    def build_reports(self, validations):
105        for func, report_key in validations:
106            try:
107                errors, warnings = func()
108                if errors or warnings:
109                    self._report_list.extend(self.TITLES_INFO[report_key], errors=errors, warnings=warnings)
110                self._errors.extend(errors)
111                self._warnings.extend(warnings)
112            except Exception as e:
113                self._report_list.extend(
114                    self.TITLES_INFO[report_key],
115                    errors=[f"Exception validation in file during {func.__name__}: {str(e)}"],
116                    warnings=[],
117                )

 47    def validate_html_in_descriptions(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 48        warnings = []
 49        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_DESC.name
 50        exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
 51        if not exists_column:
 52            return [msg_error_column], []
 53        for index, row in self._dataframe.iterrows():
 54            if re.search("<.*?>", str(row[column])):
 55                index = int(str(index))
 56                warnings.append(f"{self._filename}, linha {index + 2}: Coluna '{column}' não pode conter código HTML.")
 57        return [], warnings
 58
 59    def validate_sequential_codes(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 60        errors = []
 61
 62        # 0. Check if the column exists
 63        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
 64        exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
 65        if not exists_column:
 66            return [msg_error_column], []
 67
 68        # Load the original codes and cleaned codes
 69        original_codes = pd.to_numeric(self._dataframe[column], errors="coerce")
 70        codes_cleaned = self._data_model.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE
 71
 72        # 1. Check if the column has only integers
 73        if original_codes.size != codes_cleaned.size:
 74            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A verificação foi abortada porque a coluna '{column}' contém valores não numéricos.")
 75            return errors, []
 76
 77        # 2. Check if the first code is 1
 78        if codes_cleaned.at[0] != 1:
 79            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' deve começar em 1.")
 80
 81        # 3. Check if the codes are sequential and starting from 1
 82        if not codes_cleaned.equals(pd.Series(range(1, len(codes_cleaned) + 1))):
 83            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' deve conter valores inteiros e sequenciais (1, 2, 3, ...).")
 84
 85        return errors, []
 86
 87    def validate_unique_codes(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 88        errors = []
 89        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
 90        exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
 91        if not exists_column:
 92            return [msg_error_column], []
 93
 94        codes_cleaned = self._data_model.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE
 95        duplicated_codes = codes_cleaned[codes_cleaned.duplicated()].tolist()
 96
 97        if duplicated_codes:
 98            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' contém códigos duplicados: {duplicated_codes}.")
 99
100        return errors, []
101
102    def validate_text_capitalization(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
103        warnings = []
104        columns_to_check = [
105            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
106            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
107        ]
108
109        for column in columns_to_check:
110            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
111            if not exists_column:
112                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
113                continue
114
115            # Filter non-empty values
116            mask = self._dataframe[column].notna() & (self._dataframe[column] != "")
117            filtered_data = self._dataframe[mask]
118
119            if not filtered_data.empty:
120                # Process original text with all replacements
121                original_series = (
122                    filtered_data[column]
123                    .astype(str)
124                    .str.replace("  ", " (EXTRA_SPACE)")
125                    .str.replace("\r", "(CR)")
126                    .str.replace("\n", "(LF)")
127                    .str.replace("\x0d", "(CR)")
128                    .str.replace("\x0a", "(LF)")
129                )
130
131                # Process expected correct text with all replacements and capitalization
132                expected_series = (
133                    filtered_data[column]
134                    .astype(str)
135                    .str.replace("\r", "")
136                    .str.replace("\n", "")
137                    .str.replace("\x0d", "")
138                    .str.replace("\x0a", "")
139                    .str.strip()
140                    .apply(lambda x: capitalize_text_keep_acronyms(x.strip()))
141                )
142
143                # Find mismatches
144                mismatches_mask = original_series != expected_series
145                mismatches_indices = original_series[mismatches_mask].index
146
147                for idx in mismatches_indices:
148                    original_text = original_series.loc[idx]
149                    expected_text = expected_series.loc[idx]
150                    warnings.append(
151                        f"{self._filename}, linha {idx + 2}: Valor da coluna '{column}' fora do padrão. Esperado: '{expected_text}'. Encontrado: '{original_text}'."
152                    )
153
154        return [], warnings
155
156    def validate_indicator_levels(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
157        errors = []
158        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name
159        exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
160        if not exists_column:
161            return [msg_error_column], []
162
163        for index, row in self._dataframe.iterrows():
164            level = row[column]
165            is_valid, __ = check_cell_integer(level, min_value=1)
166            if not is_valid:
167                line_updated = int(index) + 2
168                errors.append(
169                    f"{self._filename}, linha {line_updated}: O nível do indicador na coluna '{column}' deve ser um número inteiro maior que 0."
170                )
171        return errors, []

173    def validate_punctuation(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
174        warnings = []
175        columns_dont_punctuation = [
176            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
177            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
178        ]
179        columns_must_end_with_dot = [
180            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_DESC.name,
181            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_DESC.name,
182        ]
183
184        for column in list(columns_dont_punctuation + columns_must_end_with_dot):
185            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
186            if not exists_column:
187                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
188
189        _, punctuation_warnings = check_punctuation(
190            self._dataframe,
191            self._filename,
192            columns_dont_punctuation,
193            columns_must_end_with_dot,
194        )
195        warnings.extend(punctuation_warnings)
196        return [], warnings

198    def validate_empty_strings(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
199        errors = []
200
201        columns_to_check = [
202            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
203            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
204            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_DESC.name,
205            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_DESC.name,
206        ]
207        for column in columns_to_check:
208            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
209            if not exists_column:
210                errors.append(msg_error_column)
211                continue
212            empty_rows = self._dataframe[self._dataframe[column].isna() | (self._dataframe[column] == "")].index
213            if not empty_rows.empty:
214                for index in empty_rows:
215                    errors.append(f"{self._filename}, linha {index + 2}: Nenhum item da coluna '{column}' pode ser vazio.")
216        return errors, []

218    def validate_cr_lf_characters(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
219        warnings = []
220
221        columns_start_end = self._data_model.EXPECTED_COLUMNS
222        columns_anywhere = [
223            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
224            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
225        ]
226
227        # Create an ordered dictionary with the columns
228        columns_to_check = list(OrderedDict.fromkeys(columns_anywhere + columns_start_end).keys())
229
230        # Check if the columns exist
231        for column in columns_to_check:
232            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
233            if not exists_column:
234                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
235                continue
236
237        # Run the checks for CR/LF characters
238        __, all_warnings_cr_lf = check_special_characters_cr_lf(self._dataframe, self._filename, columns_start_end, columns_anywhere)
239
240        warnings.extend(all_warnings_cr_lf)
241        return [], warnings

243    def validate_title_length(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
244        """Validate the length of titles."""
245        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name
246        max_len = SpDescription.CONSTANTS.MAX_TITLE_LENGTH
247        return self._check_text_length(column, max_len)

249    def validate_simple_description_length(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
250        """Validate the length of simple descriptions."""
251        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_DESC.name
252        max_len = SpDescription.CONSTANTS.MAX_SIMPLE_DESC_LENGTH
253        return self._check_text_length(column, max_len)

258    def run(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
259        """Runs all content validations for SpDescription."""
260        validations = [
261            (self.validate_html_in_descriptions, NamesEnum.HTML_DESC.value),
262            (self.validate_sequential_codes, NamesEnum.SC.value),
263            (self.validate_unique_codes, NamesEnum.CO_UN.value),
264            (self.validate_text_capitalization, NamesEnum.INP.value),
265            (self.validate_indicator_levels, NamesEnum.IL.value),
266            (self.validate_punctuation, NamesEnum.MAND_PUNC_DESC.value),
267            (self.validate_empty_strings, NamesEnum.EF.value),
268            (self.validate_cr_lf_characters, NamesEnum.LB_DESC.value),
269            (self.validate_simple_description_length, NamesEnum.SIMP_DESC_N.value),
270        ]
271        if self._dataframe.empty:
272            self.set_not_executed(validations)
273            return self._errors, self._warnings
274
275        # Add title length validation if the flag is not set to skip it
276        if not self._data_models_context.data_args.data_action.no_warning_titles_length:
277            validations.append((self.validate_title_length, NamesEnum.TITLES_N.value))
278
279        # BUILD REPORTS
280        self.build_reports(validations)
281
282        return self._errors, self._warnings

52            return [msg_error_column], []
53        for index, row in self._dataframe.iterrows():
54            if re.search("<.*?>", str(row[column])):
55                index = int(str(index))
56                warnings.append(f"{self._filename}, linha {index + 2}: Coluna '{column}' não pode conter código HTML.")
57        return [], warnings
def validate_sequential_codes(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]: 
59    def validate_sequential_codes(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
60        errors = []
61
62        # 0. Check if the column exists
63        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
64        exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
65        if not exists_column:
66            return [msg_error_column], []
67
68        # Load the original codes and cleaned codes
69        original_codes = pd.to_numeric(self._dataframe[column], errors="coerce")
70        codes_cleaned = self._data_model.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE
71
72        # 1. Check if the column has only integers
73        if original_codes.size != codes_cleaned.size:
74            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A verificação foi abortada porque a coluna '{column}' contém valores não numéricos.")
75            return errors, []
76
77        # 2. Check if the first code is 1
78        if codes_cleaned.at[0] != 1:
79            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' deve começar em 1.")
80
81        # 3. Check if the codes are sequential and starting from 1
82        if not codes_cleaned.equals(pd.Series(range(1, len(codes_cleaned) + 1))):
83            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' deve conter valores inteiros e sequenciais (1, 2, 3, ...).")

def validate_text_capitalization(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]: 
102    def validate_text_capitalization(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
103        warnings = []
104        columns_to_check = [
105            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
106            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
107        ]
108
109        for column in columns_to_check:
110            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
111            if not exists_column:
112                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
113                continue
114
115            # Filter non-empty values
116            mask = self._dataframe[column].notna() & (self._dataframe[column] != "")
117            filtered_data = self._dataframe[mask]
118
119            if not filtered_data.empty:
120                # Process original text with all replacements
121                original_series = (
122                    filtered_data[column]
123                    .astype(str)
124                    .str.replace("  ", " (EXTRA_SPACE)")
125                    .str.replace("\r", "(CR)")
126                    .str.replace("\n", "(LF)")
127                    .str.replace("\x0d", "(CR)")
128                    .str.replace("\x0a", "(LF)")
129                )
130
131                # Process expected correct text with all replacements and capitalization
132                expected_series = (
133                    filtered_data[column]
134                    .astype(str)
135                    .str.replace("\r", "")
136                    .str.replace("\n", "")
137                    .str.replace("\x0d", "")
138                    .str.replace("\x0a", "")
139                    .str.strip()
140                    .apply(lambda x: capitalize_text_keep_acronyms(x.strip()))
141                )
142
143                # Find mismatches
144                mismatches_mask = original_series != expected_series
145                mismatches_indices = original_series[mismatches_mask].index
146
147                for idx in mismatches_indices:
148                    original_text = original_series.loc[idx]
149                    expected_text = expected_series.loc[idx]
150                    warnings.append(
151                        f"{self._filename}, linha {idx + 2}: Valor da coluna '{column}' fora do padrão. Esperado: '{expected_text}'. Encontrado: '{original_text}'."
152                    )

 99    def validate_relation_indicators_in_values(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
100        """
101        Validate indicator relationships between values and descriptions.
102
103        Returns:
104            Tuple of (errors, warnings) lists
105        """
106        errors, warnings = [], []
107
108        if self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].empty:
109            return errors, warnings
110
111        errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(
112            required_columns={

118        if errors:

121        code_column_name = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
122        level_column_name = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name
123        scenario_column_name = SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_SCENARIO.name
124
125        # Prepare cleaned dataframes
126        # No-need to clean the values dataframe
127        df_values = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_value].copy()
128        # Need to clean the description and temporal reference dataframes
129        df_description, _ = clean_dataframe_integers(
130            self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description],
131            self.sp_name_description,
132            [code_column_name],
133        )
134
135        level_one_codes = df_description[df_description[level_column_name] == "1"][code_column_name].astype(str).tolist()
136
137        # Process value columns
138        value_columns = df_values.columns.tolist()
139        columns_to_ignore = self.global_required_columns[self.sp_name_value] + level_one_codes
140
141        valid_value_codes, invalid_columns = extract_numeric_ids_and_unmatched_strings_from_list(
142            value_columns, columns_to_ignore, self.list_scenarios
143        )
144
145        # Filter out columns containing ':'
146        processed_invalid_columns = sorted({col for col in invalid_columns if ":" not in col})
147
148        if processed_invalid_columns:
149            errors.append(f"{self.model_sp_value.filename}: Colunas inválidas: {processed_invalid_columns}.")
150
151        # Get filtered description codes using generic function
152        # Remove level 1 indicators
153        filtered_description_df = df_description[df_description[level_column_name] != "1"].copy()
154
155        # Remove level 2 indicators with scenario 0 if scenario column exists
156        if self.exists_scenario and scenario_column_name in filtered_description_df.columns:
157            filtered_description_df = filtered_description_df[
158                ~((filtered_description_df[level_column_name] == "2") & (filtered_description_df[scenario_column_name] == "0"))
159            ]
160
161        # Extract valid description codes
162        valid_description_codes, _ = extract_numeric_integer_ids_from_list(id_values_list=set(filtered_description_df[code_column_name].astype(str)))
163
164        # Compare codes between description and values
165        comparison_errors = find_differences_in_two_set_with_message(
166            first_set=valid_description_codes,
167            label_1=self.model_sp_description.filename,
168            second_set=valid_value_codes,
169            label_2=self.model_sp_value.filename,
170        )
171        errors.extend(comparison_errors)
172
173        return errors, warnings

175    def validate_value_combination_relation(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
176        """
177        Validate value combination relations between indicators and their expected columns.
178
179        This function ensures that each indicator has the correct combination of columns
180        in the values dataframe based on its level and scenario configuration.
181        """
182        errors, warnings = [], []
183
184        if self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].empty or self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_temporal_reference].empty:
185            return errors, warnings
186
187        code_column_name = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
188        level_column_name = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name
189        scenario_column_name = SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_SCENARIO.name
190        symbol_column_name = SpTemporalReference.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SYMBOL.name
191
192        local_required_columns = self.global_required_columns.copy()

197            required_columns=local_required_columns,
198            model_dataframes=self.model_dataframes,
199        )
200        if errors:
201            return errors, warnings
202
203        # Prepare cleaned dataframes
204        # No-need to clean the values dataframe
205        df_values = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_value].copy()
206
207        # Need to clean the description and temporal reference dataframes
208        df_description, _ = clean_dataframe_integers(
209            self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description],
210            self.sp_name_description,
211            local_required_columns[self.sp_name_description],
212        )
213        df_temporal_reference, _ = clean_dataframe_integers(
214            self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_temporal_reference],
215            self.sp_name_temporal_reference,
216            local_required_columns[self.sp_name_temporal_reference],
217        )
218
219        # Get temporal symbols once (sorted for consistency)
220        temporal_symbols = sorted(df_temporal_reference[symbol_column_name].unique())
221        first_year = temporal_symbols[0]
222        sp_value_columns = set(df_values.columns)
223
224        # Process each indicator efficiently
225        for _, row in df_description.iterrows():
226            code = str(row[code_column_name])
227            level = int(row[level_column_name])
228            scenario = int(row[scenario_column_name]) if self.exists_scenario else 0
229
230            # Generate expected combinations based on level and scenario
231            expected_combinations = []
232            if level >= 2:
233                if scenario == 0:
234                    expected_combinations = [f"{code}-{first_year}"]
235                elif scenario == 1:
236                    expected_combinations = generate_combinations(code, first_year, temporal_symbols, self.list_scenarios)
237
238            # Validate required combinations exist
239            for combination in expected_combinations:
240                if combination not in sp_value_columns:
241                    # Skip validation for level 2 with scenario 0 (special case)
242                    if level == 2 and scenario == 0:
243                        continue
244                    errors.append(f"{self.model_sp_value.filename}: A coluna '{combination}' é obrigatória.")
245
246            # Find actual combinations for this code
247            actual_combinations = [col for col in sp_value_columns if col.startswith(f"{code}-")]
248
249            # Check for extra combinations
250            has_extra_error, extra_columns = find_extra_combinations(expected_combinations, actual_combinations)
251            if has_extra_error:
252                for extra_column in extra_columns:
253                    if level == 1:
254                        errors.append(f"{self.model_sp_value.filename}: A coluna '{extra_column}' é desnecessária para o indicador de nível 1.")
255                    else:
256                        errors.append(f"{self.model_sp_value.filename}: A coluna '{extra_column}' é desnecessária.")
257
258        return errors, warnings

115    def validate_hierarchy_with_tree(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
116        """
117        Validate tree composition structure and detect cycles.
118
119        Returns:
120            Tuple containing (errors, warnings) lists
121        """
122        errors: List[str] = []
123        warnings: List[str] = []
124
125        # Check required columns exist
126        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(self.global_required_columns, self.model_dataframes)
127        if column_errors:

134        # Clean integer columns: df_composition
135        df_composition, _ = clean_dataframe_integers(
136            df=df_composition,
137            file_name=self.sp_name_composition,
138            columns_to_clean=[self.column_name_parent],
139            min_value=0,
140        )
141        df_composition, _ = clean_dataframe_integers(
142            df=df_composition,
143            file_name=self.sp_name_composition,
144            columns_to_clean=[self.column_name_child],
145            min_value=1,
146        )
147
148        # Clean integer columns: df_description
149        df_description, _ = clean_dataframe_integers(
150            df=df_description,
151            file_name=self.sp_name_description,
152            columns_to_clean=[self.column_name_code, self.column_name_level],
153            min_value=1,
154        )
155
156        # Add root node if not present
157        if not (df_description[self.column_name_code] == 0).any():
158            root_row = pd.DataFrame(
159                [len(self.model_sp_description.EXPECTED_COLUMNS) * [0]],
160                columns=self.model_sp_description.EXPECTED_COLUMNS,
161            )
162            df_description = pd.concat([df_description, root_row], ignore_index=True)
163
164        # Build tree and check for cycles
165        tree = create_tree_structure(df_composition, self.column_name_parent, self.column_name_child)
166
167        cycle_found, cycle = detect_tree_cycles(tree)
168        if cycle_found:
169            errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Ciclo encontrado: [{' -> '.join(cycle)}].")
170
171        # Validate level composition
172        level_errors = validate_level_hierarchy(
173            df_composition,
174            df_description,
175            self.column_name_code,
176            self.column_name_level,
177            self.column_name_parent,
178            self.column_name_child,
179        )
180
181        errors.extend(self._format_level_errors(level_errors, df_composition, df_description))
182
183        return errors, warnings
184
185    def validate_tree_levels_children(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
186        """
187        Validate that all children of the same parent have the same level.
188
189        Returns:
190            Tuple containing (errors, warnings) lists
191        """
192        errors: List[str] = []
193        warnings: List[str] = []
194
195        # Check required columns exist
196        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(self.global_required_columns, self.model_dataframes)
197        if column_errors:
198            return column_errors, warnings
199
200        df_composition = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_composition].copy()
201        df_description = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].copy()
202
203        # Create level mapping
204        levels = {row[self.column_name_code]: row[self.column_name_level] for _, row in df_description.iterrows()}
205
206        # Group by parent and validate children levels
207        parent_groups = df_composition.groupby(self.column_name_parent)
208        for parent, group in parent_groups:
209            if parent not in levels:
210                errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Código pai {parent} não encontrado na descrição.")
211                continue
212
213            children_info: List[Tuple[Any, Any]] = []
214
215            for _, row in group.iterrows():
216                child = row[self.column_name_child]
217                if child not in levels:
218                    errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Código filho {child} não encontrado na descrição.")
219                    continue
220                child_level = levels[child]
221                children_info.append((child, child_level))
222
223            if children_info and len({level for _, level in children_info}) > 1:
224                error_children = ", ".join([f"indicador {child} possui nível '{level}'" for child, level in children_info])
225                errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_description}: Indicadores filhos do pai {parent} " f"não estão no mesmo nível: [{error_children}].")
226
227        return errors, warnings
228
229    def _format_level_errors(
230        self,
231        level_errors: List[Tuple[Any, Any]],
232        df_composition: pd.DataFrame,
233        df_description: pd.DataFrame,
234    ) -> List[str]:
235        """
236        Format level composition errors with proper line numbers and descriptions.
237
238        Args:
239            level_errors: List of (parent, child) error tuples
240            df_composition: Composition dataframe
241            df_description: Description dataframe
242
243        Returns:
244            List of formatted error messages
245        """
246        formatted_errors: List[str] = []
247
248        for parent, child in level_errors:
249            if parent is not None and child is not None:
250                # Find the row with this relationship
251                matching_rows = df_composition[
252                    (df_composition[self.column_name_parent] == int(parent)) & (df_composition[self.column_name_child] == int(child))
253                ]
254
255                if not matching_rows.empty:
256                    row_index = matching_rows.index[0]
257                    line_number = row_index + 2
258
259                    parent_level = df_description[df_description[self.column_name_code] == int(parent)][self.column_name_level].values[0]
260
261                    child_level = df_description[df_description[self.column_name_code] == int(child)][self.column_name_level].values[0]
262
263                    formatted_errors.append(
264                        f"{self.sp_name_composition}, linha {line_number}: "
265                        f"O indicador {parent} (nível {parent_level}) não pode ser pai "
266                        f"do indicador {child} (nível {child_level}). "
267                        f"Atualize os níveis no arquivo de descrição."
268                    )
269
270        return formatted_errors

273        """
274        Execute all tree validation checks.
275
276        Returns:
277            Tuple containing (errors, warnings) lists
278        """

280            (self.validate_hierarchy_with_tree, NamesEnum.TH.value),
281            (self.validate_tree_levels_children, NamesEnum.CHILD_LVL.value),
282        ]
283
284        if self.model_sp_composition.data_loader_model.df_data.empty or self.model_sp_description.data_loader_model.df_data.empty:
285            self.set_not_executed(validations)
286            return self._errors, self._warnings
287
288        self.build_reports(validations)
289
290        return self._errors, self._warnings

def validate_tree_levels_children(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]: 
185    def validate_tree_levels_children(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
186        """
187        Validate that all children of the same parent have the same level.
188
189        Returns:
190            Tuple containing (errors, warnings) lists
191        """
192        errors: List[str] = []
193        warnings: List[str] = []
194
195        # Check required columns exist
196        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(self.global_required_columns, self.model_dataframes)
197        if column_errors:
198            return column_errors, warnings
199
200        df_composition = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_composition].copy()
201        df_description = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].copy()
202
203        # Create level mapping
204        levels = {row[self.column_name_code]: row[self.column_name_level] for _, row in df_description.iterrows()}
205
206        # Group by parent and validate children levels
207        parent_groups = df_composition.groupby(self.column_name_parent)
208        for parent, group in parent_groups:
209            if parent not in levels:
210                errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Código pai {parent} não encontrado na descrição.")
211                continue
212
213            children_info: List[Tuple[Any, Any]] = []
214
215            for _, row in group.iterrows():
216                child = row[self.column_name_child]
217                if child not in levels:
218                    errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Código filho {child} não encontrado na descrição.")
219                    continue
220                child_level = levels[child]
221                children_info.append((child, child_level))
222
223            if children_info and len({level for _, level in children_info}) > 1:
224                error_children = ", ".join([f"indicador {child} possui nível '{level}'" for child, level in children_info])
225                errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_description}: Indicadores filhos do pai {parent} " f"não estão no mesmo nível: [{error_children}].")
226
227        return errors, warnings

199    def validate_relations_hierarchy_with_graph(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
200        """
201        Validate tree composition structure and detect cycles.
202
203        Returns:
204            Tuple containing (errors, warnings) lists
205        """
206        errors: List[str] = []
207        warnings: List[str] = []
208
209        # Somente com dados de descricao e composicao (deve ser igual, apenas extrair)
210        local_required_columns = {
211            self.sp_name_composition: self.global_required_columns[self.sp_name_composition],
212        }
213
214        # Check required columns exist
215        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(local_required_columns, self.model_dataframes)
216        if column_errors:

220        if exists_cycle:
221            text_cycles = ""
222            for source, target in cycle:
223                text_cycles += f"{source} -> {target}, "
224            errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Ciclo encontrado: [{text_cycles[:-2]}].")
225
226        graphs_disconnected = self.graph_processing.detect_disconnected_components()
227        if graphs_disconnected:
228            list_graphs_disconnected = []
229            for i, grafo in enumerate(graphs_disconnected):
230                text_disconnected = "[" + self.graph_processing.generate_graph_report(grafo) + "]"
231                list_graphs_disconnected.append(text_disconnected)
232            errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Indicadores desconectados encontrados: " + ", ".join(list_graphs_disconnected) + ".")
233
234        return errors, warnings

236    def validate_unique_titles_with_graph(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
237        errors: List[str] = []
238        warnings: List[str] = []
239
240        if self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].empty:
241            self.set_not_executed(
242                [

244                        self.validate_unique_titles_with_graph,

255                SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
256                SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
257            ],
258        }
259
260        # Check required columns exist
261        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(local_required_columns, self.model_dataframes)
262        if column_errors:
263            return column_errors, warnings
264
265        # Create working copies and clean data
266        df_description: DataFrame = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].copy()
267        root_node = "1"
268        column_plural_simple_name = SpDescription.PluralColumn.COLUMN_PLURAL_SIMPLE_NAME.name
269        column_plural_complete_name = SpDescription.PluralColumn.COLUMN_PLURAL_COMPLETE_NAME.name
270
271        # Clean integer columns: df_description
272        df_description, _ = clean_dataframe_integers(
273            df=df_description,
274            file_name=self.sp_name_description,
275            columns_to_clean=[self.column_name_code],
276            min_value=1,
277        )
278        comparison_errors, __ = self.validate_relation_indicators_in_composition()
279        if comparison_errors:
280            return errors, warnings
281
282        existe_ciclo, __ = self.graph_processing.detect_cycles()
283        if existe_ciclo:
284            return errors, warnings
285
286        grafos_desconectados = self.graph_processing.detect_disconnected_components()
287        if grafos_desconectados:
288            return errors, warnings
289
290        # Verifica se existe pelo menos 1 nó pai == 1, senão, mostrar erro e solicitar correção
291        if not self.graph_processing.graph.has_node("1"):
292            errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Nó raiz '{root_node}' não encontrado.")
293            return errors, warnings
294
295        # Convert the graph to a tree
296        tree = self.graph_processing.convert_to_tree(root_node)
297
298        # All children of root node (1)
299        childs_root_node = list(tree.neighbors(root_node))
300
301        # Para cada filho de 1, pegar toda a sub-arvore abaixo
302        for child in childs_root_node:
303            # Rodar um BFS a partir do filho
304            sub_tree = self.graph_processing.breadth_first_search_from_node(child)
305
306            # Monta uma lista somente com os código dos nós
307            nodes = list(sub_tree.nodes())
308
309            # Busca todos um sub-dataframe de descrição com os códigos (SP_DESCRIPTION_COLUMNS.CODIGO) que estão na lista_nos
310            df_slice_description = df_description[df_description[self.column_name_code].astype(str).isin(nodes)]
311
312            # Check if the titles are unique
313            warnings_i = check_dataframe_titles_uniques(
314                dataframe=df_slice_description,
315                column_one=self.column_name_simple_name,
316                column_two=self.column_name_complete_name,
317                plural_column_one=column_plural_simple_name,
318                plural_column_two=column_plural_complete_name,
319            )
320            # Add prefix to warnings
321            warnings_i = [f"{self.sp_name_description}: {warning}" for warning in warnings_i]
322
323            # Add to main warnings list
324            warnings += warnings_i
325
326        return errors, warnings

328    def validate_associated_indicators_leafs(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
329        errors: List[str] = []
330        warnings: List[str] = []

359        df_proportionality: DataFrame = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_proportionality].copy()

361        leafs = self.graph_processing.get_leaf_nodes()
362
363        # Validation for values
364        codes_values = df_value.columns.tolist()
365        codes_values = [code.split("-")[0] for code in codes_values]
366        for leaf in leafs:

368                errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_value}: Indicador folha '{leaf}' não possui dados associados.")
369
370        # Validation for proportionality (if available)

373
374            if self.column_name_id in level_two_columns:
375                level_two_columns.remove(self.column_name_id)
376
377            level_two_columns = [col for col in level_two_columns if not col.startswith("Unnamed")]
378            level_two_columns = [col for col in level_two_columns if not col.startswith("unnamed")]
379
380            level_two_columns = [col.split("-")[0] for col in level_two_columns]
381            all_columns = list(set(level_two_columns))
382
383            # Check if all leaf codes are present in level_one_columns
384            for leaf in leafs:
385                if leaf not in all_columns:
386                    errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: Indicador folha '{leaf}' não possui dados associados.")
387        return errors, warnings

215        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(local_required_columns, self.model_dataframes)
216        if column_errors:
217            return column_errors, warnings
218
219        exists_cycle, cycle = self.graph_processing.detect_cycles()

222            for source, target in cycle:
223                text_cycles += f"{source} -> {target}, "
224            errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Ciclo encontrado: [{text_cycles[:-2]}].")

227        if graphs_disconnected:
228            list_graphs_disconnected = []
229            for i, grafo in enumerate(graphs_disconnected):
230                text_disconnected = "[" + self.graph_processing.generate_graph_report(grafo) + "]"
231                list_graphs_disconnected.append(text_disconnected)
232            errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Indicadores desconectados encontrados: " + ", ".join(list_graphs_disconnected) + ".")
233
234        return errors, warnings

130    def _check_sum_equals_one(self, subdatasets, sp_df_values):
131        errors = []
132        warnings = []
133
134        has_more_than_3_decimal_places = False
135        count_values_has_more_than_3_decimal_places = 0
136        line_init_values = 0
137
138        for parent_id, subdataset in subdatasets.items():
139
140            line_init = None
141            line_end = None
142            count_errors = 0
143            errors_column = []
144
145            for index, row in subdataset.iterrows():
146                all_cells = []
147
148                # Iterrows retorna uma tupla nome da coluna, dados da linha
149                lista_id_coluna_valor = []
150                id_linha = 0
151                # sub_col = ""
152                for i, cell in enumerate(row):
153                    # Nome da coluna
154                    nome_coluna = row.index[i]
155
156                    if i == 0:
157                        id_linha = cell
158                        continue
159
160                    lista_id_coluna_valor.append([id_linha, nome_coluna, cell])
161
162                    # Se a célula for 'self._data_models_context.config.VALUE_DI', pula para a próxima
163                    if cell == self._data_models_context.config.VALUE_DI:
164                        continue
165
166                    if pd.isna(cell) or pd.isna(pd.to_numeric(cell, errors="coerce")):
167                        if line_init is None:
168                            line_init = index + 3
169                            errors_column.append(
170                                f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}, linha {index + 3}: O valor não é um número válido e nem {self._data_models_context.config.VALUE_DI} ({self._data_models_context.config.VALUE_DATA_UNAVAILABLE.capitalize()}) para o indicador pai '{parent_id}'."
171                            )
172                        count_errors += 1
173
174                        line_end = index + 3
175                        continue
176
177                    cell_aux = cell.replace(",", ".")
178                    cell_aux = pd.to_numeric(cell_aux, errors="coerce")
179
180                    # Trunca o valor para 3 casas decimais
181                    new_value = truncate_number(cell_aux, 3)
182                    a = Decimal(str(cell))
183
184                    # Verifica se o valor tem mais de 3 casas decimais
185                    if a.as_tuple().exponent < -3:
186                        if not has_more_than_3_decimal_places:
187                            line_init_values = index + 3
188                        has_more_than_3_decimal_places = True
189                        count_values_has_more_than_3_decimal_places += 1
190
191                    all_cells.append(str(new_value))
192
193                # Soma os valores válidos da linha
194                row_sum = sum([Decimal(cell) for cell in all_cells])
195
196                if row_sum == 0:
197                    for data in lista_id_coluna_valor:
198                        id_linha, id_coluna, valor = data
199
200                        try:
201                            valor = sp_df_values.loc[sp_df_values[self.column_name_id] == id_linha][id_coluna].values[0]
202                            if valor != self._data_models_context.config.VALUE_DI and float(valor) != 0:
203                                errors.append(
204                                    f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: A soma de fatores influenciadores para o ID '{id_linha}' no pai '{id_coluna}' é 0 (zero). Na planilha {self.sp_name_value}, existe(m) valor(es) para os filhos do indicador '{id_coluna}', no mesmo ID, que não é (são) zero ou DI (Dado Indisponível)."
205                                )
206
207                        except Exception:
208                            continue
209                elif row_sum < Decimal("0.99") or row_sum > Decimal("1.01"):
210
211                    errors.append(
212                        f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}, linha {index + 3}: A soma dos valores para o indicador pai {parent_id} é {format_number_brazilian(row_sum, self._data_models_context.lm.current_language)}, e não 1."
213                    )
214                elif row_sum != 1 and Decimal("0.99") <= row_sum <= Decimal(
215                    "1.01"
216                ):  # elif row_sum != 1 and row_sum >= Decimal('0.99') and row_sum <= Decimal('1.01'):
217                    warnings.append(
218                        f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}, linha {index + 3}: A soma dos valores para o indicador pai {parent_id} é {format_number_brazilian(row_sum, self._data_models_context.lm.current_language)}, e não 1."
219                    )
220            if count_errors > 1:
221                errors_column.clear()
222                errors_column.append(
223                    f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: {count_errors} valores que não são número válido nem {self._data_models_context.config.VALUE_DI} ({self._data_models_context.config.VALUE_DATA_UNAVAILABLE.capitalize()}) para o indicador pai '{parent_id}' entre as linhas {line_init} e {line_end}."
224                )
225
226            errors.extend(errors_column)
227
228        if has_more_than_3_decimal_places:
229            text_existem = "Existem" if count_values_has_more_than_3_decimal_places > 1 else "Existe"
230            text_valores = "valores" if count_values_has_more_than_3_decimal_places > 1 else "valor"
231            warnings.append(
232                f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}, linha {line_init_values}: {text_existem} {count_values_has_more_than_3_decimal_places} {text_valores} com mais de 3 casas decimais, serão consideradas apenas as 3 primeiras casas decimais."
233            )
234
235        return errors, warnings

403    def validate_parent_child_relationships(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
404        errors, warnings = [], []
405        if self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_composition].empty:
406            self.set_not_executed(
407                [
408                    (
409                        self.validate_parent_child_relationships,
410                        NamesEnum.IND_VAL_PROP.value,
411                    )
412                ]
413            )
414            return errors, warnings
415
416        # Somente com dados de descricao e composicao (deve ser igual, apenas extrair)
417        local_required_columns = {
418            self.sp_name_proportionality: self.global_required_columns[self.sp_name_proportionality],
419            self.sp_name_composition: self.global_required_columns[self.sp_name_composition],
420        }
421
422        # Check required columns exist
423        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(local_required_columns, self.model_dataframes)
424        if column_errors:
425            return column_errors, warnings
426
427        # Setup dataframes
428        df_proportionalities = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_proportionality].copy()
429        df_composition = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_composition].copy()
430
431        # Build subdatasets
432        subdatasets = build_subdatasets(df_proportionalities, self.column_name_id)
433
434        # Filter composition to remove level 1 parents
435        df_composition = df_composition[df_composition[self.column_name_parent] != "1"]
436
437        dict_grouped_composition = {}
438        for __, row in df_composition.iterrows():
439            parent = row[self.column_name_parent]
440            child = row[self.column_name_child]
441
442            if parent not in dict_grouped_composition:
443                dict_grouped_composition[parent] = []
444
445            dict_grouped_composition[parent].append(child)
446
447        for parent_id, subdataset in subdatasets.items():
448
449            cleaned_parent_id = parent_id.split("-")[0]
450
451            if cleaned_parent_id not in dict_grouped_composition.keys():
452                if ":" not in parent_id:
453                    errors.append(
454                        f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: O indicador pai '{cleaned_parent_id}' (em '{parent_id}') não está presente na coluna '{self.column_name_parent}' da planilha {self.sp_name_composition}."
455                    )
456                continue
457
458            children_codes = [col for col in subdataset.columns.tolist() if not col.lower().startswith(self.column_name_id)]
459            children_codes_cleaned = [filho.split("-")[0] for filho in children_codes]
460
461            dict_children_codes_cleaned = dict()
462            dict_children_codes_cleaned.setdefault(cleaned_parent_id, []).extend(children_codes_cleaned)
463
464            set_errors = {
465                f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: O indicador '{filho}' (em '{filho_orig}') não é filho do indicador '{cleaned_parent_id}' (em '{parent_id}') conforme especificado em {self.sp_name_composition}."
466                for filho, filho_orig in zip(children_codes_cleaned, children_codes)
467                if filho not in dict_grouped_composition[cleaned_parent_id]
468            }
469            errors.extend(set_errors)
470
471            for child in dict_grouped_composition[cleaned_parent_id]:
472                if child not in dict_children_codes_cleaned[cleaned_parent_id]:
473                    code_pai_local = parent_id.split("-")[0]
474                    errors.append(
475                        f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: Deve existir pelo menos uma relação do indicador filho '{child}' com o indicador pai '{code_pai_local}' (em '{parent_id}') conforme especificado em {self.sp_name_composition}."
476                    )
477
478        errors = sorted(set(errors))
479
480        return errors, warnings

515    def run(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
516        """Runs all content validations for SpProportionality."""
517
518        validations = [
519            (self.validate_relation_indicators_in_proportionality, NamesEnum.IR.value),
520            (self.validate_columns_repeated_indicators, NamesEnum.REP_IND_PROP.value),
521            (self.validate_relation_indicators_in_value_and_proportionality, NamesEnum.IND_VAL_PROP.value),
522            (self.validate_parent_child_relationships, NamesEnum.IR_PROP.value),
523            (self.validate_sum_properties_in_influencing_factors, NamesEnum.SUM_PROP.value),
524        ]
525        if self._dataframe.empty:
526            self.set_not_executed(validations)
527            return self._errors, self._warnings
528
529        # BUILD REPORTS
530        self.build_reports(validations)
531
532        return self._errors, self._warnings

403    def validate_parent_child_relationships(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
404        errors, warnings = [], []
405        if self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_composition].empty:
406            self.set_not_executed(
407                [
408                    (
409                        self.validate_parent_child_relationships,
410                        NamesEnum.IND_VAL_PROP.value,
411                    )
412                ]
413            )
414            return errors, warnings
415
416        # Somente com dados de descricao e composicao (deve ser igual, apenas extrair)
417        local_required_columns = {
418            self.sp_name_proportionality: self.global_required_columns[self.sp_name_proportionality],
419            self.sp_name_composition: self.global_required_columns[self.sp_name_composition],
420        }
421
422        # Check required columns exist
423        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(local_required_columns, self.model_dataframes)
424        if column_errors:
425            return column_errors, warnings
426
427        # Setup dataframes
428        df_proportionalities = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_proportionality].copy()
429        df_composition = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_composition].copy()
430
431        # Build subdatasets
432        subdatasets = build_subdatasets(df_proportionalities, self.column_name_id)
433
434        # Filter composition to remove level 1 parents
435        df_composition = df_composition[df_composition[self.column_name_parent] != "1"]
436
437        dict_grouped_composition = {}
438        for __, row in df_composition.iterrows():
439            parent = row[self.column_name_parent]
440            child = row[self.column_name_child]
441
442            if parent not in dict_grouped_composition:
443                dict_grouped_composition[parent] = []
444
445            dict_grouped_composition[parent].append(child)
446
447        for parent_id, subdataset in subdatasets.items():
448
449            cleaned_parent_id = parent_id.split("-")[0]
450
451            if cleaned_parent_id not in dict_grouped_composition.keys():
452                if ":" not in parent_id:
453                    errors.append(
454                        f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: O indicador pai '{cleaned_parent_id}' (em '{parent_id}') não está presente na coluna '{self.column_name_parent}' da planilha {self.sp_name_composition}."
455                    )
456                continue
457
458            children_codes = [col for col in subdataset.columns.tolist() if not col.lower().startswith(self.column_name_id)]
459            children_codes_cleaned = [filho.split("-")[0] for filho in children_codes]
460
461            dict_children_codes_cleaned = dict()
462            dict_children_codes_cleaned.setdefault(cleaned_parent_id, []).extend(children_codes_cleaned)
463
464            set_errors = {
465                f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: O indicador '{filho}' (em '{filho_orig}') não é filho do indicador '{cleaned_parent_id}' (em '{parent_id}') conforme especificado em {self.sp_name_composition}."
466                for filho, filho_orig in zip(children_codes_cleaned, children_codes)
467                if filho not in dict_grouped_composition[cleaned_parent_id]
468            }
469            errors.extend(set_errors)
470
471            for child in dict_grouped_composition[cleaned_parent_id]:
472                if child not in dict_children_codes_cleaned[cleaned_parent_id]:
473                    code_pai_local = parent_id.split("-")[0]
474                    errors.append(
475                        f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: Deve existir pelo menos uma relação do indicador filho '{child}' com o indicador pai '{code_pai_local}' (em '{parent_id}') conforme especificado em {self.sp_name_composition}."
476                    )
477
478        errors = sorted(set(errors))
479
480        return errors, warnings

 68    def validate_spellchecker(self, model_class: Type[Union[SpDescription, SpTemporalReference, SpScenario]]) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 69        """
 70        Generic spellchecker validation method that works with any model class.
 71
 72        Args:
 73            model_class: The model class to validate (e.g., SpDescription, SpTemporalReference, SpScenario)
 74
 75        Returns:
 76            Tuple containing lists of errors and warnings
 77        """
 78        errors, warnings = [], []
 79
 80        # Configure local instances
 81        self._data_model = self._data_models_context.get_instance_of(model_class)
 82        self._dataframe = self._data_model.data_loader_model.df_data.copy()
 83        self._filename = self._data_model.filename
 84
 85        if self._dataframe.empty:
 86            return errors, warnings
 87
 88        # Get columns to check for this model
 89        columns_to_check = self.model_columns_map.get(model_class, [])
 90
 91        if not columns_to_check:
 92            # If no columns defined for this model, skip validation
 93            return errors, warnings
 94
 95        # Check if the columns exist
 96        for column in columns_to_check:
 97            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
 98            if not exists_column:
 99                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
100                continue
101
102        # Perform spellcheck
103        errors_spellchecker, warnings_spellchecker = self.spellchecker.check_spelling_text(
104            df=self._dataframe,
105            file_name=self._filename,
106            columns_sheets=columns_to_check,
107        )
108
109        errors.extend(sorted(errors_spellchecker))
110        warnings.extend(sorted(warnings_spellchecker))
111
112        return errors, warnings
113
114    def _prepare_statement(self):
115        if self.spellchecker.errors_dictionary:
116            self._errors.extend(self.spellchecker.errors_dictionary)
117
118    def run(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
119        """Runs all content validations for SpScenario."""
120
121        validations = []
122        if not self._data_models_context.data_args.data_action.no_spellchecker:
123            # Add validation for Description
124            validations.append(
125                (
126                    lambda: self.validate_spellchecker(SpDescription),
127                    NamesEnum.SPELL.value,
128                )
129            )
130
131            # Add validation for Temporal Reference
132            validations.append(
133                (
134                    lambda: self.validate_spellchecker(SpTemporalReference),
135                    NamesEnum.SPELL.value,
136                )
137            )
138
139            # Add validation for Scenario if scenarios exist
140            if self._data_model.scenarios_list:
141                validations.append(
142                    (
143                        lambda: self.validate_spellchecker(SpScenario),
144                        NamesEnum.SPELL.value,
145                    )
146                )
147
148        # BUILD REPORTS
149        self.build_reports(validations)
150
151        # Cleanup temporary files
152        self.spellchecker.clean_files_generated()
153
154        return self._errors, self._warnings

def validate_spellchecker( self, model_class: Type[Union[data_validate.models.SpDescription, data_validate.models.SpTemporalReference, data_validate.models.SpScenario]]) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]: 
 68    def validate_spellchecker(self, model_class: Type[Union[SpDescription, SpTemporalReference, SpScenario]]) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 69        """
 70        Generic spellchecker validation method that works with any model class.
 71
 72        Args:
 73            model_class: The model class to validate (e.g., SpDescription, SpTemporalReference, SpScenario)
 74
 75        Returns:
 76            Tuple containing lists of errors and warnings
 77        """
 78        errors, warnings = [], []
 79
 80        # Configure local instances
 81        self._data_model = self._data_models_context.get_instance_of(model_class)
 82        self._dataframe = self._data_model.data_loader_model.df_data.copy()
 83        self._filename = self._data_model.filename
 84
 85        if self._dataframe.empty:
 86            return errors, warnings
 87
 88        # Get columns to check for this model
 89        columns_to_check = self.model_columns_map.get(model_class, [])
 90
 91        if not columns_to_check:
 92            # If no columns defined for this model, skip validation
 93            return errors, warnings
 94
 95        # Check if the columns exist
 96        for column in columns_to_check:
 97            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
 98            if not exists_column:
 99                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
100                continue
101
102        # Perform spellcheck
103        errors_spellchecker, warnings_spellchecker = self.spellchecker.check_spelling_text(
104            df=self._dataframe,
105            file_name=self._filename,
106            columns_sheets=columns_to_check,
107        )
108
109        errors.extend(sorted(errors_spellchecker))
110        warnings.extend(sorted(warnings_spellchecker))
111
112        return errors, warnings

 61    def check_empty_directory(self) -> tuple[bool, List[str]]:
 62        """
 63        Check if the input directory is empty.
 64
 65        Returns:
 66            bool: True if the directory is empty, False otherwise.
 67        """
 68        local_errors = []
 69        is_empty, message = self.context.fs_utils.check_directory_is_empty(self.context.data_args.data_file.input_folder)
 70        if is_empty:
 71            local_errors.append(
 72                self.context.lm.text(
 73                    "validator_structure_error_empty_directory",
 74                    dir_path=self.context.data_args.data_file.input_folder,
 75                )
 76            )
 77        return not local_errors, local_errors
 78
 79    def check_not_expected_files_in_folder_root(self) -> tuple[bool, List[str]]:
 80        """
 81        Check for unexpected folders or files in the input directory.
 82        """
 83        local_errors = []
 84        expected_files = self.context.config.EXPECTED_FILES
 85        optional_files = self.context.config.OPTIONAL_FILES
 86
 87        if len(self.dir_files) == 1:
 88            dir_path = os.path.join(self.context.data_args.data_file.input_folder, self.dir_files[0])
 89            is_dir, _ = self.context.fs_utils.check_directory_exists(dir_path)
 90            if is_dir:
 91                local_errors.append(self.context.lm.text("validator_structure_error_files_not_in_folder"))
 92                return not local_errors, local_errors
 93
 94        for file_name in self.dir_files:
 95            file_path = os.path.join(self.context.data_args.data_file.input_folder, file_name)
 96            is_file, _ = self.context.fs_utils.check_file_exists(file_path)
 97            if not is_file:
 98                local_errors.append(self.context.lm.text("validator_structure_error_unexpected_folder").format(file_name=file_name))
 99                continue
100
101            file_base, file_ext = os.path.splitext(file_name)
102            if file_base in expected_files and file_ext in expected_files[file_base]:
103                continue
104            if file_base in optional_files and file_ext in optional_files[file_base]:
105                continue
106
107            local_errors.append(self.context.lm.text("validator_structure_error_unexpected_file").format(file_name=file_name))
108
109        return not local_errors, local_errors
110
111    def check_expected_files_in_folder_root(self) -> tuple[bool, List[str]]:
112        """
113        Check if all expected files are present in the input directory.
114        """
115        local_errors = []
116        expected_files = self.context.config.EXPECTED_FILES
117
118        for file_base, extensions in expected_files.items():
119            file_found = False
120            for ext in extensions:
121                file_path = os.path.join(self.context.data_args.data_file.input_folder, f"{file_base}{ext}")
122                is_file, _ = self.context.fs_utils.check_file_exists(file_path)
123                if is_file:
124                    file_found = True
125                    break
126            if not file_found:
127                local_errors.append(self.context.lm.text("validator_structure_error_missing_file").format(file_base=file_base))
128        return not local_errors, local_errors
129
130    def check_ignored_files_in_folder_root(self) -> tuple[bool, List[str]]:
131        """
132        Check for files that will be ignored in the root folder.
133        Emit an error if both .xlsx and .csv files with the same name exist.
134        """
135        local_errors = []
136        file_groups = {}
137
138        for file_name in self.dir_files:
139            file_base, file_ext = os.path.splitext(file_name)
140            if file_ext in [".xlsx", ".csv"]:
141                if file_base not in file_groups:
142                    file_groups[file_base] = []
143                file_groups[file_base].append(file_ext)
144
145        for file_base, extensions in file_groups.items():
146            if ".xlsx" in extensions and ".csv" in extensions:
147                local_errors.append(self.context.lm.text("validator_structure_error_conflicting_files").format(file_base=file_base))
148
149        return not local_errors, local_errors
150
151    def validate_all_general_structure(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
152        """
153        Perform all validation checks on the input folder.
154
155        Returns:
156            List[str]: A list of validation errors.
157        """
158        all_errors = [
159            [self.check_empty_directory()],
160            [self.check_not_expected_files_in_folder_root()],
161            [self.check_expected_files_in_folder_root()],
162            [self.check_ignored_files_in_folder_root()],
163        ]
164        for check in all_errors:
165            is_valid, errors = check[0]
166            if not is_valid:
167                self.errors.extend(errors)
168
169        return self.errors, []

181        return self._errors, self._warnings
